cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video-to-video synthesis, which is a task related to image and video processing. The paper also proposes a novel network weight generation module utilizing an attention mechanism, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses several large-scale video datasets, which could also place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with human-dancing videos, talking-head videos, and street-scene videos, which could also place it under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
